            <title>[PIG-3747] Update skewed join documentation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3747</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While working on Tez skewed join, I found two problems with the skewed join documentation-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The following is misleading because skewed join also works with left, right, and full outer joins.
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Skewed join works with two-table inner join. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In two-way join, the 1st table must be the skewed one because Pig samples on that. But this is not mentioned anywhere.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</description>
